{"id":15294,"date":"2022-04-21T18:03:20","date_gmt":"2022-04-21T11:03:20","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/?p=15294"},"modified":"2022-04-21T18:03:23","modified_gmt":"2022-04-21T11:03:23","slug":"vietnamese-traditional-wedding-ceremony-from-the-eyes-of-jewish","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/vietnamese-traditional-wedding-ceremony-from-the-eyes-of-jewish\/","title":{"rendered":"Vietnamese Traditional Wedding Ceremony From The Eyes Of Jewish"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-d9d5efb\" data-block-id=\"d9d5efb\"><style>.stk-d9d5efb{padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-d9d5efb{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-d9d5efb{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-d9d5efb-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-853ce3c\" data-block-id=\"853ce3c\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-853ce3c-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-853ce3c-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p>Jewish and Vietnamese \u2013 This seems like an odd comparison since One is the people of a religion while the other is the people of a country. However, this blog will not bring you a comparison of a Jewish Wedding and Vietnamese wedding but rather bringing you the point of view of Jewish on Vietnamese traditional wedding ceremony.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both Jewish v\u00e0 Vietnamese have their very own distinctive traditions which are completely different to each other. What interesting about Vietnamese culture is that there are some customs that have been formed for hundred years and continued till modern times with no sign of being neglected. No matter if they are a Christian or a Buddhist, there are some Vietnamese traditions that can be missed. One of those is the traditional wedding customs including: Ask for the bride Ceremony and Pick up the bride Ceremony.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this blog, we would like to focus on the experiences of a Jewish family when they first time attended a Vietnamese traditional wedding ceremony and they were not any of the guests, they represented the groom side. Both the groom and the groom\u2019s father have their very own thoughts about Vietnamese traditional wedding ceremony which could bring another point of view of Vietnamese traditions and helps you \u2013 foreigners \u2013 those who like to know more about our culture and especially those who are about to tie the knot with Vietnamese.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Talking about the background of the couple, the bride \u2013 Thuong is Vietnamese. She \u2013 was born and raised in a rich cultural family in Hanoi \u2013 the capital of Vietnam. Growing up, she turns into a modern, international women. Thuong travels a lot and has spent years living in Singapore, Isreal, America and other countries. She met her husband \u2013 Max in America \u2013 a young business man who is successfull at a very young age. Max was born and raised in America and he is a Jewish.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-0369-1.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15333\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-605e6de\" data-block-id=\"605e6de\"><style>.stk-605e6de{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-605e6de{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-605e6de{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-605e6de-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-fcf3af0\" data-block-id=\"fcf3af0\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-fcf3af0-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-fcf3af0-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>Ask for the bride Ceremony is the Vietnamese wedding traditional ceremony that is equivalent to an engagement on the couple\u2019s marriage between the two families<\/em>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last October, Max and his family had come a long way to Vietname to officially tie the knot with Thuong. Among of Max\u2019s family and friends, this is the very first time they came to Vietnam and of course, the very first time, they attended a Vietnamese traditional wedding ceremony.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-0669.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15303\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-fe1e014\" data-block-id=\"fe1e014\"><style>.stk-fe1e014{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-fe1e014{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-fe1e014{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-fe1e014-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-07e7999\" data-block-id=\"07e7999\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-07e7999-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-07e7999-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>The Max\u2019s family prepare gifts for the bride\u2019s family when they come to her home. The Gift is a symbol of the groom\u2019s family\u2019s gratitude to the bride\u2019s family for raising their daughter.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After the ceremony, we had some questions for Max and his family about how they feel about the ceremony. We got some very interesting answers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is Evan\u2019s thoughts on the ceremony. He is the father of Max \u2013 the groom.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1140.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15307\"><figcaption><em>Heading to the bride\u2019s house on \u201cx\u00edch l\u00f4\u201d \u2013 signature vehicle of Hanoi.<\/em><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-12091.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15315\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-9dcd1d3\" data-block-id=\"9dcd1d3\"><style>.stk-9dcd1d3{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-9dcd1d3{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-9dcd1d3{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-9dcd1d3-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-00f433c\" data-block-id=\"00f433c\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-00f433c-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-00f433c-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>Max and his groomsmen wore \u201c\u00c1o D\u00e0i\u201d \u2013 traditional costume of Vietnamese in the Ask for the bride Ceremony. Their \u00c1o D\u00e0i were tailored months before the ceremony.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FROM THE FATHER OF THE GROOM<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>\u201c<em>For me, the traditional Vietnamese wedding was the highlight of our trip to Vietnam and I am very grateful to Ong Thien and Ba Ha (the parents of the bride) for making this possible. There were four aspects of the ceremony that made it special for me:<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1228.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15309\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-0fc7a22\" data-block-id=\"0fc7a22\"><style>.stk-0fc7a22{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-0fc7a22{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-0fc7a22{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-0fc7a22-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-f4b3c46\" data-block-id=\"f4b3c46\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-f4b3c46-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-f4b3c46-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>The groomsmen have an important role as they assist the groom\u2019s family to carry the gifts to the bride\u2019s&nbsp;house.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1231.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15337\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-0499513\" data-block-id=\"0499513\"><style>.stk-0499513{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-0499513{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-0499513{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-0499513-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-422f4da\" data-block-id=\"422f4da\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-422f4da-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-422f4da-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>The bride family welcomes the groom family in front of their house. In this ceremony, women will wear \u00c1o D\u00e0i while men will\u00a0dress with a suit.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1264.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15339\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-80f13e6\" data-block-id=\"80f13e6\"><style>.stk-80f13e6{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-80f13e6{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-80f13e6{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-80f13e6-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-57e9c33\" data-block-id=\"57e9c33\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-57e9c33-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-57e9c33-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>The bride\u2019s family\u2019s acceptance of the gift signifies their approval of the marriage. The bridesmaids will take the gift from the groomsmens.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1236-1.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15311\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1555.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15347\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-04caa1b\" data-block-id=\"04caa1b\"><style>.stk-04caa1b{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-04caa1b{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-04caa1b{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-04caa1b-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-5c6c611\" data-block-id=\"5c6c611\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-5c6c611-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-5c6c611-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>\u201cFirst was the focus on family. On opposite sides of a long table sat two families who were more dissimilar than similar. It didn\u2019t matter that both families did not speak the same language. It didn\u2019t matter that the two families came from completely different cultures and wedding practices. What transcended these differences to bind the members of each family together on the wedding day was their shared love for the couple. The gathering at the table and the exchange of remarks reinforced the belief that the marriage is more than two people coming together. It\u2019s a marriage of two families.\u201d\u00a0<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1333.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15341\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-df164e6\" data-block-id=\"df164e6\"><style>.stk-df164e6{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-df164e6{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-df164e6{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-df164e6-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-87a2e2a\" data-block-id=\"87a2e2a\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-87a2e2a-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-87a2e2a-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>At the \u201cAsk for the bride Ceremony, the two family will officially meet each other, sit down together and talk about the marriage of the couple.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1074.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15305\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-44973d6\" data-block-id=\"44973d6\"><style>.stk-44973d6{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-44973d6{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-44973d6{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-44973d6-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-05b902c\" data-block-id=\"05b902c\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-05b902c-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-05b902c-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>The bride\u2019s family will decorate their house to greet the groom\u2019s family. They also prepare some delicous favors to treat the groom\u2019s family during the ceremony.<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>\u201cSecond was the observance of tradition. From the procession to the Ao Dai, the giving of the gifts and the exchange of introductions and remarks by the family, the Vietnamese ceremony offered a rich set of traditional practices. The Ao Dai of the bridegrooms and the bridesmaids were truly celebratory but my favorites were the Ao Dai of the bride and groom. For me, the bride\u2019s phoenix represented the continual re-birth and never-ending duration of their love and the groom\u2019s dragon meant to reinforce the strength of the couple\u2019s love. The symbolism of these traditions gave the ceremony a heightened sense of significance.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1364.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15343\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1434.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15345\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1562-1.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15349\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-a12737f\" data-block-id=\"a12737f\"><style>.stk-a12737f{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-a12737f{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-a12737f{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-a12737f-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-cbb2ea2\" data-block-id=\"cbb2ea2\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-cbb2ea2-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-cbb2ea2-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>The representatives of the two families ( in most case, will be the father) will have some speeches, introducing their family members and talk about the main purpose of the ceremony.\u00a0The families will make an announcement about the couple\u2019s marriage to their extended families.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1371.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15313\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-2ab9ddc\" data-block-id=\"2ab9ddc\"><style>.stk-2ab9ddc{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-2ab9ddc{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-2ab9ddc{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-2ab9ddc-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-0b4f56c\" data-block-id=\"0b4f56c\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-0b4f56c-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-0b4f56c-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>\u201cFourth, I tried to learn how to speak enough Vietnamese so that I could recite my part of the ceremony in Vietnamese rather than in my native English. I felt that extending this effort was a special way that I could show my respect and thanks to Thuong\u2019s family for hosting us. I was surprised how difficult it was to learn the correct pronunciation but that made it all the more valuable.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1666-5.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15351\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-faf8c06\" data-block-id=\"faf8c06\"><style>.stk-faf8c06{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-faf8c06{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-faf8c06{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-faf8c06-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-8e7e585\" data-block-id=\"8e7e585\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-8e7e585-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-8e7e585-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><em>During the Ceremony, the bride will stay in her room. The groom will come to her room and pick her up after receiving the acceptance of her parents.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1674.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15295\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-83918e3\" data-block-id=\"83918e3\"><style>.stk-83918e3{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-83918e3{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-83918e3{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-83918e3-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-53eb568\" data-block-id=\"53eb568\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-53eb568-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-53eb568-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p>\u201c<em>Unlike the Jewish wedding, the Vietnamese ceremony had a formal procession, an exchange of gifts and at least a figurative gesture of the bride coming to the groom\u2019s house. Despite all of these differences, at the core are common principles that a) the union transcends the two individuals and encompasses the family as the central unit and b) the practice of traditions that have evolved over centuries enrich the event. Each family shares a strong commitment to the importance of family and enjoying a life with rich cultural traditions.\u201d<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1843.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15297\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-0753.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15335\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-5ea2044\" data-block-id=\"5ea2044\"><style>.stk-5ea2044{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-5ea2044{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-5ea2044{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-5ea2044-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-e23aba8\" data-block-id=\"e23aba8\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-e23aba8-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-e23aba8-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p>That is the Evan\u2019s thought on Vietnamese traditional wedding ceremony and his son \u2013 Max \u2013 the groom also has some of his own thoughts on his Vietnamese. Here is his answers on some of our questions about the ceremony.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FROM THE GROOM<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Max, can you share with us &nbsp;the differences between Vietnamese<\/em><\/strong><strong><em>&nbsp;and Jewish<\/em><\/strong>&nbsp;<strong><em>wedding customs<\/em><\/strong><strong><em>?<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>The Vietnamese&nbsp;<\/em><em>wedding is more intimate since the ceremony happens at the bride\u2019s parents\u2019 house; while the Jewish ceremony happens in an open\/mutual space. The guests at<\/em><em>&nbsp;the Vietnamese wedding ceremony are close families and very few close friends, while it can be a bigger group at the Jewish wedding.<\/em><em>&nbsp;The second difference is that there is no religious remark in Vietnamese weddings; the ceremony is led by a family member; while a<\/em>&nbsp;<em>rabbi typically officiates the Jewish ceremony and there are several religious rituals throughout the ceremony. And the third difference that I observed is that the bride only appears in the second half of a Vietnamese ceremony, but in a Jewish ceremony, she will be there from the beginning until the end.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-2064-1.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15299\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-1acd07a\" data-block-id=\"1acd07a\"><style>.stk-1acd07a{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-1acd07a{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-1acd07a{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-1acd07a-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-95b9bd8\" data-block-id=\"95b9bd8\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-95b9bd8-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-95b9bd8-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><strong><em>What is the thing that you find most interesting ( or meaningful) in the Ask for the bride Ceremony?<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>The \u201cask for the bride\u201d and the \u201cdon dau\u201dceremonies emphasize a lot that the marriage is the joining of the two families; and the ceremonies themselves are more about the two families, not just about the bride and the groom. I think that is a very important thing to remember.<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-2083-1.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15301\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-1d097ac\" data-block-id=\"1d097ac\"><style>.stk-1d097ac{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-1d097ac{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-1d097ac{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-1d097ac-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-5d31449\" data-block-id=\"5d31449\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-5d31449-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-5d31449-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><strong><em>Do your friends and your family share any of their thoughts on the Ask for the bride Ceremony.&nbsp;<\/em><\/strong><strong><em>Did they enjoy it?<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>My family is beyond happy. It was a very unique experience to them. Everything was so colorful, Thuong\u2019s family and her Vietnamese friends are very friendly and welcoming, we got to participate and understand the Vietnamese traditions. Everything was new to us, we\u2019ve never experienced anything like this before. My brothers were really excited to carry the tr\u00e1p on the x\u00edch l\u00f4, my mom loved her Ao dai; she was amazed by the skill of the tailor, my dad was very honored to lead my side of the family at the ceremony. And the rest of the family enjoyed every minute of it. It was definitely one of the most important and special experiences for my family so far.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1887-1-1.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15319\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1179.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15321\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-2287e78\" data-block-id=\"2287e78\"><style>.stk-2287e78{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-2287e78{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-2287e78{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-2287e78-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-93da610\" data-block-id=\"93da610\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-93da610-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-93da610-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p><strong><em>I see you wearing the Ao Dai \u2013 Vietnamese traditional costume. What do you think about it?&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/em><\/strong><strong><em>Do you feel comfortable in it :D?<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-1137.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15323\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-dcf3e8f\" data-block-id=\"dcf3e8f\"><style>.stk-dcf3e8f{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-dcf3e8f{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-dcf3e8f{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-dcf3e8f-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-9798079\" data-block-id=\"9798079\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-9798079-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-9798079-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p>I love the Ao Dai, I am very happy that I get to wear one \u2013 and wear it with the hat! It is important for me to show respect to Thuong\u2019s culture this way. I also think the Ao Dai has more \u201cpersonalities\u201d than the western tuxedo. It is very colorful, and it is very comfortable to wear. I hope to wear it again at traditional Vietnamese occasions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>What did you think when you saw your bride in the Ao Dai?<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It was like an expected surprise. I\u2019ve never seen Thuong in ao dai, only in modern, casual clothes. I\u2019ve seen her mom, her friends in Ao dai \u2013 through photos Thuong showed me; but I can not imagine someone who is very international like Thuong in such a traditional outfit. She looked so beautiful in it! When I saw her, I saw a beautiful Vietnamese lady and I totally understand why she has been insisting to have a custom-made one and why she\u2019s been so excited to put it on.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-0565.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15325\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018HAThuongMaxHanoi-1583.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15327\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-2436.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15329\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2048\" height=\"1365\" src=\"https:\/\/theplannersvn.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/1018AJSThuongMaxHanoi-2012.jpg\" alt=\"-\" class=\"wp-image-15331\"><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-columns stk-block-columns stk-block stk-08f9503\" data-block-id=\"08f9503\"><style>.stk-08f9503{padding-top:5em !important;padding-right:5em !important;padding-bottom:5em !important;padding-left:5em !important;margin-bottom:0% !important}@media screen and (max-width:1024px){.stk-08f9503{padding-top:3em !important;padding-right:3em !important;padding-bottom:3em !important;padding-left:3em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}@media screen and (max-width:767px){.stk-08f9503{padding-top:0em !important;padding-right:0em !important;padding-bottom:0em !important;padding-left:0em !important;margin-bottom:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-row stk-inner-blocks has-text-align-center stk-block-content stk-content-align stk-08f9503-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-stackable-column stk-block-column stk-column stk-block stk-4066cec\" data-block-id=\"4066cec\"><style>@media screen and (max-width:1025px){.stk-4066cec-container{margin-top:20px !important;margin-right:0px !important;margin-bottom:20px !important;margin-left:0px !important}}<\/style><div class=\"stk-column-wrapper stk-block-column__content stk-container stk-4066cec-container stk--no-background stk--no-padding\"><div class=\"stk-block-content stk-inner-blocks\">\n<p>We find it interesting to see Vietnamese traditional wedding ceremony through the eyes of foreigners who has completely different cultures and customs. And what beautiful here is that no matter how great the diferences in cultures of a mixed couple are, they still find empathy, respect and a strong connection between them.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Jewish and Vietnamese \u2013 This seems like an odd comparison since One is the people of a religion while the other is the people of a country. However, this blog will not bring you a comparison of a Jewish Wedding and Vietnamese wedding but rather bringing you the point of view of Jewish on Vietnamese [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected"